I continue to be fascinated by the role of chief compliance officer at a ra=
nsomware company.=C2=A0In general, the chief compliance officer at any comp=
any has a dial in front of her that she can turn to get More Crime or Less =
Crime, and at a normal company =E2=80=94=C2=A0a bank, for instance =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0her job consists of (1) turning it most of the way toward Less Cri=
me, but (2) not all the way, and (3) acting very contrite when politicians =
and regulators yell at her about the residual crime. =E2=80=9CWe have a zer=
o-tolerance policy for crime,=E2=80=9D she will say, and almost mean.
But the chief compliance officer at a ransomware company =E2=80=94=C2=A0I a=
ssume that this is not an actual job, but rather one of many hats worn by s=
ome senior executive at the ransomware company, though what do I know =E2=
=80=94=C2=A0will turn the dial=C2=A0most=C2=A0of the way toward More Crime,=
 since after all a ransomware company=E2=80=99s whole business is crime, bu=
t, again, not all the way. Sometimes=C2=A0she will say no to crime, or at l=
east act very contrite after doing crime. She will have, like, a 98% tolera=
nce policy for crime.
We have  talked about this before, and one category of crime that a ransomw=
are compliance officer might reject is =E2=80=9Chacks that are so big and d=
isastrous that they could call down the wrath of the US government and shut=
 down the whole business.=E2=80=9D But another category of off-limits crime=
 appears to be =E2=80=9Chacks that are so morally reprehensible that they w=
ill lead to other criminals boycotting your business.=E2=80=9D Here is a wi=
ld story about  a ransomware attack on Toronto=E2=80=99s Hospital for Sick =
Children, which is really the sort of name that ought to make you immune fr=
om hacking:

A global ransomware operator issued an apology and offered to unlock the da=
ta targeted in a ransomware attack on Toronto=E2=80=99s Hospital for Sick C=
hildren, a move cybersecurity experts say is rare, if not unprecedented, fo=
r the infamous group.
LockBit, a ransomware group the U.S. Federal Bureau of Investigation has ca=
lled one of the world=E2=80=99s most active and destructive, issued the bri=
ef apology on Dec. 31 to what cybersecurity experts say is the dark web pag=
e where it posts about its ransoms and data leaks.
In the statement, reviewed directly by The Canadian Press, LockBit claimed =
to have blocked the =E2=80=9Cpartner=E2=80=9D responsible for the attack an=
d offered SickKids a free decryptor to unlock its data. =E2=80=A6
LockBit=E2=80=99s apology, meanwhile, appears to be a way of managing its i=
mage, said [cybersecurity researcher Chester] Wisniewski.
The group is competing with other high-profile malware operators who are al=
so trying to court hackers to use their system to carry out lucrative cyber=
attacks, he said. Hackers appear to move between the operators frequently.
He suggested the move could be directed at those partners who might see the=
 attack on a children=E2=80=99s hospital as a step too far.
=E2=80=9CMy instinct would be this is more aimed at criminal affiliates the=
mselves trying to not disgust them into switching into a different ransom g=
roup,=E2=80=9D said Wisniewski.

The way the ransomware business is organized seems to be that there are a c=
ouple of, like, malware-as-a-service providers like LockBit and DarkSide th=
at provide software and expertise to independent hacker customers who pick =
the targets and do the hacks; the providers and the hackers split the ranso=
ms. If you are one of the providers, you have to choose your hacker partner=
s carefully so that they do the right amount of crime: You don=E2=80=99t wa=
nt incompetent or unambitious hackers who can=E2=80=99t make any money, but=
 you also don=E2=80=99t want overly ambitious hackers who hack, you know, t=
he US Department of Defense, or the=C2=A0Hospital for Sick Children. Meanwh=
ile you also have to market yourself to hacker partners so that they choose=
 your services, which again requires that you have a reputation for being g=
ood and bold at crime, but not=C2=A0too=C2=A0bold. Your hacker partners wan=
t to do crime, but they have their limits, and if you get a reputation for =
murdering sick children that will cost you some criminal=C2=A0business.

