adding=3D"0">
<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Private markets don=E2=80=99t like to go down</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusin=
ess.com/click/30164362.280519/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL=
2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDEtMDQvcHJpdmF0ZS1tYXJrZXRzLWRvbi10LWxpa2UtdG8tZ28tZG93=
bj9jbXBpZD1CQkQwMTA1MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U=
9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzAxMDUmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07=
ceef4b8524a319a23cB50d59fea" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope"=
 target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importan=
t; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-st=
yle: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  talked yesterday</a> about an enduri=
ng appeal of private investing =E2=80=94=C2=A0venture capital, private equi=
ty, non-traded real estate, etc. =E2=80=94=C2=A0which is that, when the sto=
ck market goes down, your private investments don=E2=80=99t have to. If you=
 own public stocks, those stocks trade every day, and if their prices go do=
wn then your portfolio is worth less. If you own private investments, they =
don=E2=80=99t trade every day, so you have a lot of flexibility in how you =
mark them to market. You can look at discounted cash flow analyses and publ=
ic comparables and appraisals and=C2=A0recent fundraising rounds and come t=
o some estimate of the value, but that estimate might be less volatile than=
 a public stock price. And so=C2=A0if you are a hedge fund that owns a bunc=
h of public tech stocks and a bunch of private tech stocks, and the public =
stocks go down by 20%, you can say things like =E2=80=9Cour large private h=
oldings to some extent insulated us from the downturn in public markets,=E2=
=80=9D and skeptical journalists and investors can say things like =E2=80=
=9Cwell, did they really?=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Obviously there are limits to this, and if the=
re is a sustained downturn in public markets because economic conditions ha=
ve gotten worse and tech companies have a harder time raising money, you ev=
entually have to mark down the private stakes too. But you still have some =
room to argue about how much they are worth, and some incentives to make th=
at number high.=C2=A0Here is a <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusine=
ss.com/click/30164362.280519/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9ncmFwaGljcy=
8yMDIzLWhlZGdlLWZ1bmRzLXByaXZhdGUtY29tcGFueS1zaGFyZS12YWx1YXRpb24vP2NtcGlkP=
UJCRDAxMDUyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0=
dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDEwNSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524=
a319a23cB62e6e6ea" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D=
"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-=
bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid=
; background-color: #ccc;">  Bloomberg News story</a> about how hedge funds=
 and mutual funds have been marking their private tech stakes differently:<=
/p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The pain =E2=80=94 and then the questions =E2=
=80=94 kept coming last year as prominent hedge funds took turns marking do=
wn the value of their stakes in private companies. Every time they wrote do=
wn holdings by millions, or even billions, of dollars, investors questioned=
 whether they had gone far enough. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Five mega-hedge fund firms =E2=80=94 Tiger Glo=
bal Management, D1 Capital Partners, Lone Pine Capital, Viking Global Inves=
tors and Coatue Management =E2=80=94 all ramped up their bets on startups i=
n the past few years, wagering that soaring valuations and a hot market for=
 initial public offerings would reap massive rewards. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Dozens of the companies they bought into are a=
lso owned by mutual funds run by the likes of Fidelity and T. Rowe Price th=
at are required to disclose valuations regularly. Mutual funds have been ma=
rking down some holdings even more severely than the drop in public markets=
.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Mining data from thousands of mutual funds ove=
r the past year, Bloomberg tracked down their valuations for 46 private com=
panies that also count the five hedge fund firms as investors. Of those, ab=
out 70% of the private companies had been marked down by mutual funds throu=
gh September last year, with an average decline of 35%. Some holdings were =
slashed by as much as 85%. =E2=80=A6=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In some cases, the data show hedge fund marks =
haven=E2=80=99t caught up.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Obviously you can raise your eyebrows at the h=
edge funds here, but there are some arguments that the hedge funds have it =
right:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Compared with mutual funds, hedge =
funds tend to be more sophisticated investors with greater influence at the=
 startups they buy into. They may negotiate special terms for their stakes,=
 such as representation on boards or preferential treatment in future fundi=
ng rounds or an anti-dilution clause. Money managers who purchase large sta=
kes or buy directly, instead of in the secondary market, may also get more =
frequent updates on the venture=E2=80=99s performance. All of that can impa=
ct valuations.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Mutual funds offer an interesting =
comparison because they typically give clients more liquidity =E2=80=94 the=
 ability to buy and sell anytime markets are open. That incentivizes mutual=
 funds to update asset values quickly, taking potentially more aggressive m=
arkdowns, so that clients who withdraw aren=E2=80=99t overpaid. In contrast=
, hedge fund clients can typically pull cash quarterly, and venture and pri=
vate equity ones may be locked in for years.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you run a mutual fund, a high mark is good =
for investors who=C2=A0<em>take money out</em>, while a low mark is good fo=
r investors who=C2=A0<em>keep money in</em>.<a class=3D"footnote-index" hre=
f=3D"#footnote-4" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important=
; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-sty=
le: none !important; background-color: transparent !important; display: inl=
ine-block;">
<span>[4]</span>
</a>=C2=A0In conditions of uncertainty, you might be tempted to use a low m=
ark to reward your loyal investors. If you run a hedge fund, the main tempt=
ation is to report better performance.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also yesterday, in writing about these incenti=
ves,=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30164362=
.280519/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDE=
tMDQvcHJpdmF0ZS1tYXJrZXRzLWRvbi10LWxpa2UtdG8tZ28tZG93bj9jbXBpZD1CQkQwMTA1Mj=
NfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fd=
GVybT0yMzAxMDUmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cC50d=
59fea" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" sty=
le=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width=
: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background=
-color: #ccc;">I said</a> that venture capitalists do not like down rounds =
because =E2=80=9Cthey have to tell their own investors that they lost money=
 for them; their assets under management have gone down and they can=E2=80=
=99t charge as much in fees.=E2=80=9D That was a sloppy thing to say; in fa=
ct private investment funds normally charge management fees based on commit=
ted capital or investments at cost, and performance fees based on realized =
returns, so fees on existing assets don=E2=80=99t directly motivate how the=
y mark their assets. But the main point is that reporting good performance =
to their investors <em>is=C2=A0</em>a motivator, and marking down investmen=
ts hurts with that. And marking up helps. A=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.ma=
il.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30164362.280519/aHR0cHM6Ly9wYXBlcnMuc3Nybi5j=
b20vc29sMy9wYXBlcnMuY2ZtP2Fic3RyYWN0X2lkPTM4NTE4MTk/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23=
cBb4134489" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank=
" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-=
width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backg=
round-color: #ccc;">2021 paper</a> by Peter Pham, Nick Turner and Jason Zei=
n finds =E2=80=9Cthat venture capitalists (VCs) strategically enhance their=
 current funds=E2=80=99 interim performance around new fundraising events=
=E2=80=9D: They =E2=80=9Ctend to invest in follow-on financing rounds of th=
eir existing portfolio firms at abnormally high step-ups in valuation=E2=80=
=9D when they are in the process of raising a new fund, because good interi=
m performance impresses investors and bad performance does not.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Elsewhere in <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloo=
mbergbusiness.com/click/30164362.280519/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2x=
lcy92ZW50dXJlLWZpcm1zLXN0cmF0ZWd5LW9mLWhvbGRpbmctc3RvY2tzLWZvci1sb25nZXItYm=
Fja2ZpcmVzLWR1cmluZy1tYXJrZXQtcm91dC0xMTY3Mjg5ODg4OA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a2=
3cB7fc8e44a" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blan=
k" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom=
-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; back=
ground-color: #ccc;"> venture capital and public versus private markets</a>=
:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Venture-capital firms that deployed a new stra=
tegy of holding stocks for longer have come to regret it amid last year=E2=
=80=99s market rout.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">During the recent bull market, venture-capital=
 investors that typically exit a stock after taking it public held on to th=
eir shares in the hope of maximizing returns. Instead, the sharp selloff in=
 technology stocks in 2022 has dealt a punishing blow to that strategy. Som=
e of the splashiest startup stocks from 2021 plunged, making it unlikely th=
ose investors will recover the value of their earlier positions anytime soo=
n, if at all.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That=E2=80=99s the thing about public markets,=
 sometimes=C2=A0they go down.</p>
