<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Ransomware compliance</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I continue to be fascinated by the role of chi=
ef compliance officer at a ransomware company.=C2=A0In general, the chief c=
ompliance officer at any company has a dial in front of her that she can tu=
rn to get More Crime or Less Crime, and at a normal company =E2=80=94=C2=A0=
a bank, for instance =E2=80=94=C2=A0her job consists of (1) turning it most=
 of the way toward Less Crime, but (2) not all the way, and (3) acting very=
 contrite when politicians and regulators yell at her about the residual cr=
ime. =E2=80=9CWe have a zero-tolerance policy for crime,=E2=80=9D she will =
say, and almost mean.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But the chief compliance officer at a ransomwa=
re company =E2=80=94=C2=A0I assume that this is not an actual job, but rath=
er one of many hats worn by some senior executive at the ransomware company=
, though what do I know =E2=80=94=C2=A0will turn the dial=C2=A0<em>most=C2=
=A0</em>of the way toward More Crime, since after all a ransomware company=
=E2=80=99s whole business is crime, but, again, not all the way. <em>Someti=
mes</em>=C2=A0she will say no to crime, or at least act very contrite after=
 doing crime. She will have, like, a 98% tolerance policy for crime.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We have <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/30164362.280519/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGlu=
aW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDUtMTEvY3J5cHRvLW1hcmtldHMtYXJlLXdoZXJlLXRoZS1mdW4=
taXM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDEwNTIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cm=
NlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwMTA1JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f=
07ceef4b8524a319a23cB91ba6ecd" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscop=
e" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !import=
ant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-=
style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> talked about this before</a>, and o=
ne category of crime that a ransomware compliance officer might reject is =
=E2=80=9Chacks that are so big and disastrous that they could call down the=
 wrath of the US government and shut down the whole business.=E2=80=9D But =
another category of off-limits crime appears to be =E2=80=9Chacks that are =
so morally reprehensible that they will lead to other criminals boycotting =
your business.=E2=80=9D Here is a wild story about <a href=3D"https://link.=
mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30164362.280519/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuY2FuYWRpYW=
51bmRlcndyaXRlci5jYS9pbnN1cmFuY2UvcmFuc29td2FyZS1ncm91cC1hcG9sb2dpemVzLXNhe=
XMtcGFydG5lci13YXMtYmVoaW5kLXNpY2traWRzLWF0dGFjay0xMDA0MjI5MjI5Lw/607f07cee=
f4b8524a319a23cB8e05918e" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" ta=
rget=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; =
border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style=
: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> a ransomware attack on Toronto=E2=80=99s=
 Hospital for Sick Children</a>, which is really the sort of name that ough=
t to make you immune from hacking:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A global ransomware operator issued an apology=
 and offered to unlock the data targeted in a ransomware attack on Toronto=
=E2=80=99s Hospital for Sick Children, a move cybersecurity experts say is =
rare, if not unprecedented, for the infamous group.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">LockBit, a ransomware group the U.S. Federal B=
ureau of Investigation has called one of the world=E2=80=99s most active an=
d destructive, issued the brief apology on Dec. 31 to what cybersecurity ex=
perts say is the dark web page where it posts about its ransoms and data le=
aks.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In the statement, reviewed directly by The Can=
adian Press, LockBit claimed to have blocked the =E2=80=9Cpartner=E2=80=9D =
responsible for the attack and offered SickKids a free decryptor to unlock =
its data. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">LockBit=E2=80=99s apology, meanwhile, appears =
to be a way of managing its image, said [cybersecurity researcher Chester] =
Wisniewski.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The group is competing with other high-profile=
 malware operators who are also trying to court hackers to use their system=
 to carry out lucrative cyberattacks, he said. Hackers appear to move betwe=
en the operators frequently.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">He suggested the move could be directed at tho=
se partners who might see the attack on a children=E2=80=99s hospital as a =
step too far.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CMy instinct would be this is more aim=
ed at criminal affiliates themselves trying to not disgust them into switch=
ing into a different ransom group,=E2=80=9D said Wisniewski.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The way the ransomware business is organized s=
eems to be that there are a couple of, like, malware-as-a-service providers=
 like LockBit and DarkSide that provide software and expertise to independe=
nt hacker customers who pick the targets and do the hacks; the providers an=
d the hackers split the ransoms. If you are one of the providers, you have =
to choose your hacker partners carefully so that they do the right amount o=
f crime: You don=E2=80=99t want incompetent or unambitious hackers who can=
=E2=80=99t make any money, but you also don=E2=80=99t want overly ambitious=
 hackers who hack, you know, the US Department of Defense, or the=C2=A0<em>=
Hospital for Sick Children</em>. Meanwhile you also have to market yourself=
 to hacker partners so that they choose your services, which again requires=
 that you have a reputation for being good and bold at crime, but not=C2=A0=
<em>too=C2=A0</em>bold. Your hacker partners want to do crime, but they hav=
e their limits, and if you get a reputation for murdering sick children tha=
t will cost you some criminal=C2=A0business.</p>
